#
# This file is deliberately empty of entries.
#
# /etc/aliases is NOT in postfix's runtime lookup chain here:
#   - alias_maps = regexp:/etc/postfix/aliases_regexp   (the only thing
#     postfix consults for local alias expansion)
#   - alias_database is unset (default would be hash:/etc/aliases, but
#     since nothing references that hash at runtime, it doesn't matter)
#
# aliases_regexp is a catch-all (`/.*/  egnor@ofb.net`) so every local
# recipient at a mydestination domain — postmaster, root, admin, info,
# anything — already forwards to egnor@ofb.net. Adding entries here would
# be silently ignored.
#
# To route a name to a different place, edit aliases_regexp (and put the
# specific match ahead of the `.*` catch-all).
